		<TD BGCOLOR="#BEA279" width="470">
		<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
		
		<DIV ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="+2">Ranger Ivy Etched Armor</FONT><BR>
Zone : Kithicor<BR><BR>
<TABLE CELLSPACING = 0 CELLPADDING = 0 BORDER = 0>
<TR><TD><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="ariel"><B>Updated</B> November 13th 1999<BR>
<B>Submitted</B> by Multam Weatherlight, 20th Ranger of Tarew Marr</FONT><BR><BR>

In the ranger camp in Kithicor (apx /loc +1460,+2316) you can obtain several pieces of Ranger only armor: <BR><BR>

<A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=122">Ivy Etched Tunic:</A> (Gandari) You need a Skull of Meldrath (from Steamfont Mino Caves), the right side of the Rune of Ivy (from Thistle Brownie in Lesser Faydark and 2 rubies. <BR><BR>

<A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=123">Ivy Etched Helm:</A> (Gandari) You need the top of the Rune of Ivy (from a Deathly Usher in Mistmoore), a Cyclops Charm (from Tarskuk in Rathe Mtns) and 1 Sapphire. <BR><BR>

<A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=124">Ivy Etched Sleeves:</A> (Gandari) You need a Heart of Fire (from an Inferno Goblin in Solusek), the left Rune of Ivy (from Griffon Grimfether in Karanas) and 2 star rubies. <BR><BR>

<A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=126">Ivy Etched Bracer:</A> (Gandari) You need the bottom of the Rune of Ivy (from Orc named Redwind in Everfrost), a watery ring (from a Tidal Lord in Dagnor's Cauldron) and 1 fire emerald. <BR><BR>

<B>Ivy Etched Gauntlets:</B> (NPC outside by tree) Hunt Maldyn Greenburn (a wayward  master archer) in the Rathe Mountains near the Unkept Druids and retreive Morin's Bow of Kithicor. (NPC hints at the bow being very powerful) <BR><BR>

<A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=218">Ivy Etched Boots:</A>  (Leaf Falldim) You need Ronium (see below),a Mistmoore Granite (from Gargoyles in Mistmoore) and 2000 gp. <BR><BR>

<A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=127">Ivy Etched Leggings:</A>  (Leaf Falldim) Leaf needs the "Quiver of Kithicor" and a Star of Odus, which can be purchased in Erudin.  To get the quiver, go to Kelethin and speak with Leutenant Leafstalker who tells you to collect 6 different named arrows (Acknowledgment, Bravery, Defiance, Gallantry, Fortitude and Recognition) from the Outcast Brownies in Lesser Faydark (Kill Pixe Tricksters and Pranksters to get them to spawn).  Then go to OOT and to Seafury Isle. Kill the Buccaners until Miltin the thief spawns (he is a very rare spawn) and kill him, hoping that he drops the Quiver. Get the Quiver and combine the 6 Arrows.  Return the Quiver to Leaf in Kithicor along with the star. <BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel">
<B>How to make Ronium:</B><BR><BR>

You need to talk to Lord Searfire, the Dwarven Smith in The Temple of Solusek Ro. He must consider you warmly before he will deal with you.  He will then give you the Sol Cauldron and tell you how to do the next step, which is acquiring the ingredients to make the metal ronium.  These are: <BR><BR>

<B>-Melatite</B> (buy from Gnomes in Solusek - also sometimes dropped by some clockworks in Ak'Anon), <BR>
<B>-Two Bars of Enchanted Platinum,</B><BR>
<B>-Mistmoore Granite</B> (from Gargoyles in Mistmoore),<BR>
<B>-Sands of Ro</B> (from sand giants) and<BR>
<B>-Soil of Underfoot</B> (Get from Priestess Ghalea in the Kaladim cleric's guild for 4 fairy dusts
[need very high faction for this]).  Put them in the cauldron and hit the combine button and you will get a bar of Ronium.  I have been told that it is necessary for you to have a high blacksmithing skill to do this.</FONT><BR><BR>

<B>NEW:</B> Click <A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/files/ranger_armor.zip">HERE</A> to download a single page checklist for this quest that is in Word '97 format. A handy tool to help organize all the steps involved.<BR><BR>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
